# Keep the Docker build context minimal and free of anything that is not a
# tracked production source. Only go.mod, cmd/, and internal/ are COPYied by the
# Dockerfile; this file is defense in depth so stray local state, secrets, or
# test scaffolding can never enter an image layer even if the Dockerfile changes.

# Tests and scaffolding are never part of the production image.
**/*_test.go

# Docs and deploy assets are not build inputs.
README.md
deploy/
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# Local runtime, secrets, and agent/code-intelligence state (belt and braces;
# these live at the repo root, outside this module context, but are excluded
# explicitly in case of future layout changes).
.env
.env.*
secrets/
credentials/
auths/
data/
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
.ref/
.scratch/
.codegraph/
.codex/
.claude/
.agents/

# Build artifacts.
bin/
dist/
coverage.out
*.test
*.prof
